            <div class="opener__topic-title-dek-wrapper ">

                    <span class="opener__topics ">
            <a class="opener__topics-link " href="https://www.propublica.org/topics/immigration">Immigration</a>
        </span>
    
    <h1 class="opener__hed " >        How Shifting U.S. Policies Led to One of the Deadliest Incidents Involving Immigrants in Mexico’s History
    </h1>

    <h2 class="opener__dek " >        A year ago, 40 men were killed in a detention center fire in Ciudad Juárez, Mexico. A ProPublica-Texas Tribune examination shows that landmark shifts in U.S. border policies helped sow the seeds of a tragedy.
    </h2>

    </div> <!-- Close .opener__topic-title-dek-wrapper -->

</div>
        
<div class="article-meta-1
     article-meta-1--left     " data-pp-location="article meta">

    <span class="article-meta-1__byline" data-pp-location="article byine">
        by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/perla-trevizo">Perla Trevizo</a>    </span>
    <time class="article-meta-1__pubdate">
        <time class="timestamp" datetime="2024-05-01EDT06:00">May 1, 5 a.m. CDT</time>
    </time>

